  levelNumber: 12
  levelName: "Yaxh\xE1"
  location: "Pet\xE9n, Guatemala"
  levelDescription: "By blue-green waters, pyramids and ballcourts echoed with the
    voices of a thriving Maya city.\n\nYaxha, meaning \u201CBlue-Green Water\u201D
    in Maya, was one of the largest cities in the Pet\xE9n region of Guatemala. Rising
    on a ridge beside Lake Yaxha, it thrived during the Preclassic and Classic periods
    (c. 600 BC\u2013900 AD).\r\n\r\nThe site holds over 500 structures, including
    nine pyramids, two ballcourts, and many altars and stelae. Its plazas were connected
    by sacbeob (raised stone roads), showing how the Maya linked sacred spaces. At
    its height, Yaxha was the third-largest city in the region, rivaling nearby Tikal
    and Nakum"
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: fb2e24eedf7c270459be7ddf73e0001d, type: 3}
